annotationA: Eukaryotic translation initiation factor 5; Catalyzes the hydrolysis of GTP bound to the 40S ribosomal initiation complex (40S.mRNA.Met-tRNA[F].eIF-2.GTP) with the subsequent joining of a 60S ribosomal subunit resulting in the release of eIF-2 and the guanine nucleotide. The subsequent joining of a 60S ribosomal subunit results in the formation of a functional 80S initiation complex (80S.mRNA.Met-tRNA[F]) (By similarity)
annotationB: eIF2B-epsilon, isoform A; Nucleotidyltransferase activity; guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor activity; translation initiation factor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: translational initiation
